"{\"uid\": \"finanznachrichten.de-nachrichten-2024-07-62861655-start-io-analysis-oregon-sending-highest-number-of-american-tourists-to-summer-olympics-per-capita-200.htm\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Nearly 13% of American tourists in Paris live in Oregon, Start.io analysis reveals  NEW YORK, NY / ACCESSWIRE / July 30, 2024 /Oregonians are traveling to Paris for the Summer Olympics in higher numbers than expected, according to a new data analysis from Start.io.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"score\": 0.846434175924841, \"rank\": 0.1804148831439857, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999842712998148, \"rank\": 1.5728947632428957e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.9998041809019056, \"rank\": 0.00018676986448235518, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\"}, {\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999470192066, \"rank\": 5.298086946461973e-08, \"text\": \"NEW YORK, NY\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999842712998148, \"rank\": 1.5728947632428957e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This tiny state in the Northwest is home to an estimated 4.23 million Americans, or roughly 1.3% of the nation's population.\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 290, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Northwest\", \"score\": 0.9950201050792313, \"rank\": 0.005003388808750778, \"text\": \"Northwest\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Northwest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Northwest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Oregonians make up nearly 13% of the Americans currently in Paris for the opening week of the Summer Games, according to Start.io data.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999842712998148, \"rank\": 1.5728947632428957e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In its analysis, Start.io studied a representative sample of more than 50,000 American tourists in Paris between July 18 and July 28, 2024, ranked by their home state.\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"score\": 0.846434175924841, \"rank\": 0.1804148831439857, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999842712998148, \"rank\": 1.5728947632428957e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Start.io delivers hundreds of millions of ads each day to more than 500,000 active mobile apps, and gathers anonymized consumer data, including location.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisers can use location data from Start.io to send targeted ads to people who are traveling.\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other states that have a higher-than-expected number of American tourists per capita include Washington state, New Jersey, California, and New York.\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"score\": 0.846434175924841, \"rank\": 0.1804148831439857, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9294827362999876, \"rank\": 0.06268186468823371, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Washington\"}, {\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.9999997564339379, \"rank\": 2.4322796671685703e-07, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}, {\"begin\": 1077, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9991639923536676, \"rank\": 0.0005491753063668332, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.8723361302231717, \"rank\": 0.14634651975058335, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\